Instructions for Roll & Score: Dice Duel

Objective: The goal of the game is to be the first player to reach a total score of 100 points or more.

Setup:

Two players take turns rolling a dice.
Each player starts with a score of 0.
The game begins with Player 1.
Gameplay:

On your turn, click the "Roll Dice" button to roll the dice.
If you roll a 1, you lose all your current points, and it becomes the next player's turn.
If you roll a number other than 1, that number gets added to your current score.
You can continue rolling as many times as you like in a turn.
Click "Hold" to add your current score to your total score and end your turn.
Winning:

The game continues until one player's total score reaches 100 or more.
The player who reaches or exceeds 100 points first wins the game.
The winner is declared, and the game ends.
Starting a New Game:

At any point, you can click the "New Game" button to start a fresh game.
This will reset all scores and start a new game with Player 1.
Enjoy the game and have fun rolling the dice!




